# Power BI Dashboard Project

## Overview
This project presents an interactive Power BI dashboard built using data retrieved from a SQL database. The dashboard provides meaningful insights through visualizations, KPI tracking, and trend analysis, helping users make data-driven decisions.

## Features
- Interactive dashboard with filters and slicers
- Key Performance Indicators (KPIs)
- Dynamic charts and graphs
- Data exploration through drill-down functionality
- Real-time analysis of SQL data

## Technologies Used
- Power BI
- SQL
- Power Query
- DAX (Data Analysis Expressions)

## Dataset
The data is extracted from a SQL database using custom SQL queries. The dataset contains structured records that are transformed and loaded into Power BI for analysis.

## Data Processing
1. Connected Power BI to the SQL database.
2. Executed SQL queries to retrieve required data.
3. Cleaned and transformed data using Power Query.
4. Created relationships between tables.
5. Developed calculated columns and measures using DAX.
6. Built interactive visualizations and reports.

## Dashboard Components
- KPI Cards
- Bar Charts
- Line Charts
- Pie/Donut Charts
- Tables and Matrices
- Slicers and Filters

